      "id": "line-000",
      "start": 0.0,
      "end": 6.06,
      "text": "This is a LibraVox recording. All LibraVox recordings are in the public domain.",
      "note": ""
    },
    {
      "id": "line-001",
      "start": 7.0,
      "end": 11.6,
      "text": "For more information, or to volunteer, please visit LibraVox.org.",
      "note": ""
    },
    {
      "id": "line-002",
      "start": 12.72,
      "end": 16.24,
      "text": "Recorded by Ted McElroy, Austin, Texas.",
      "note": ""
    },
    {
      "id": "line-003",
      "start": 18.54,
      "end": 21.22,
      "text": "Esop's Fables, the Man and the Image.",
      "note": ""
    },
    {
      "id": "line-004",
      "start": 22.58,
      "end": 27.64,
      "text": "A poor man had a wooden image of a god to which he used to pray daily for riches.",
      "note": ""
    },
    {
      "id": "line-005",
      "start": 27.64,
      "end": 31.96,
      "text": "He did this for a long time, but remained as poor as ever.",
      "note": ""
    },
    {
      "id": "line-006",
      "start": 32.66,
      "end": 38.56,
      "text": "Till one day he caught up the image in disgust and hurled it with all his strength against the wall.",
      "note": ""
    },
    {
      "id": "line-007",
      "start": 39.16,
      "end": 44.68,
      "text": "The force of the blow split open the head, and a quantity of gold coins fell out upon the floor.",
      "note": ""
    },
    {
      "id": "line-008",
      "start": 45.38,
      "end": 49.86,
      "text": "The man gathered them up greedily and said, Oh, you old fraud, you.",
      "note": ""
    },
    {
      "id": "line-009",
      "start": 50.3,
      "end": 56.32,
      "text": "When I honored you, you did me no good whatever. But no sooner do I treat you to insults and violence",
      "note": ""
    },
    {
      "id": "line-010",
      "start": 56.32,
      "end": 62.12,
      "text": "than you make a rich man of me. End of the man and the image.",
      "note": ""
    }
  ],
